00:59:21,758 --> 00:59:24,784
and most likely demoted
for putting you on the case.

777
00:59:27,030 --> 00:59:30,898
This whole thing has been
embarrassing enough, Megan.

778
00:59:34,904 --> 00:59:37,134
But it makes no sense.

779
00:59:37,173 --> 00:59:39,767
Do you know what everyone calls her?

780
00:59:42,245 --> 00:59:44,372
Beth.

781
00:59:44,414 --> 00:59:46,541
You told me that already.

782
00:59:51,788 --> 00:59:53,881
Now where was the gun, Meg?

783
00:59:57,594 --> 00:59:58,856
Norcross on TV:
Good evening.

784
00:59:58,895 --> 01:00:01,921
We believe that the man who the press
labeled as the Alphabet Killer

785
01:00:01,965 --> 01:00:03,956
was shot and killed this evening.

786
01:00:04,000 --> 01:00:06,628
Suspect's name was Len Schaefer.

787
01:00:06,669 --> 01:00:08,796
He was an employee of
the Webster Fire Department.

788
01:00:08,838 --> 01:00:11,898
He may have been using
a fireman's uniform

789
01:00:11,941 --> 01:00:14,535
to lure his victims into his vehicle.

790
01:00:14,577 --> 01:00:16,875
When the police arrived
on the scene this evening

791
01:00:16,913 --> 01:00:18,972
he was holding
a young lady at gunpoint,

792
01:00:19,015 --> 01:00:22,109
a young lady who had
double initials in her name.

793
01:00:22,151 --> 01:00:24,381
Suspect was allegedly trying

794
01:00:24,420 --> 01:00:26,388
to rape the young lady
when the police intervened.

795
01:00:26,422 --> 01:00:29,755
He brandished a weapon at the officers.

796
01:00:29,792 --> 01:00:32,260
The officers shot and killed him.

797
01:00:32,295 --> 01:00:35,230
The young lady suffered no injuries.

798
01:00:35,264 --> 01:00:36,959
She's recovering well.

799
01:00:37,000 --> 01:00:39,867
We're still gathering evidence,
but I think it's safe to say

800
01:00:39,902 --> 01:00:43,565
that this dark chapter in our community's
history is coming to an end.

801
01:00:43,606 --> 01:00:45,403
Are there any questions?

802
01:00:54,250 --> 01:00:56,377
Oh!

803
01:01:00,056 --> 01:01:01,580
I wanted to catch you
before you left.

804
01:01:01,624 --> 01:01:03,455
- Mmm.
- You okay?

805
01:01:05,628 --> 01:01:07,926
Hey, Megan...

806
01:01:07,964 --> 01:01:11,058
I wanted to say it was actually

807
01:01:11,100 --> 01:01:13,466
nice working with you.

808
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:15,733
I'm sorry it ended this way.

809
01:01:15,772 --> 01:01:17,933
No, it's all right.

810
01:01:17,974 --> 01:01:20,841
I've still got my job
in the records department.

811
01:01:20,877 --> 01:01:22,742
For now.

812
01:01:26,783 --> 01:01:29,445
You don't think Len Schaefer
committed those murders, do you?

813
01:01:32,121 --> 01:01:35,557
I don't know.
It's certainly not the way I imagined it.

814
01:01:35,591 --> 01:01:37,821
Are you still on the case?

815
01:01:37,860 --> 01:01:40,727
Another week or two
to close the files.

816
01:01:42,398 --> 01:01:43,888
It's been a tough one, Meg.

817
01:02:07,090 --> 01:02:09,024
Did you mean that?

818
01:02:10,993 --> 01:02:13,461
Sorry.
No.

819
01:02:13,496 --> 01:02:15,521
I don't think so.

820
01:02:15,565 --> 01:02:18,728
- I'm... I'm just really...
- It's okay. It's okay.

821
01:02:20,203 --> 01:02:22,433
No need to explain.

822
01:02:22,472 --> 01:02:24,633
I'll see you soon.

823
01:03:52,795 --> 01:03:54,786
Megan: I just have a few questions
about the abduction

824
01:03:54,831 --> 01:03:56,924
so that I could tie up
some loose ends.

825
01:03:56,966 --> 01:04:00,060
You know, I'm surprised
you're still on the job.

826
01:04:00,102 --> 01:04:03,037
But of course we'll share
any information we have.

827
01:04:03,072 --> 01:04:06,041
Now that you got the collar.

828
01:04:06,075 --> 01:04:08,270
That's correct.

829
01:04:09,946 --> 01:04:13,143
Um, when did you know

830
01:04:13,182 --> 01:04:15,912
that the Alphabet Killer
was Len Schaefer?

831
01:04:18,254 --> 01:04:21,849
He assaulted a young girl,
a young girl with double initials.

832
01:04:21,891 --> 01:04:24,416
The color of his personal car matched.

833
01:04:24,460 --> 01:04:28,260
And when the tests from the cat hair
came back positive

834
01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:31,698
we were pretty sure that confirmed it.

835
01:04:31,734 --> 01:04:35,067
Your men found the cat hair
when they searched Len's house?

836
01:04:36,505 --> 01:04:39,668
First the car then the house, yes.

837
01:04:39,709 --> 01:04:42,576
Mmm, I saw some as well.

838
01:04:42,612 --> 01:04:44,273
The cat hair.

839
01:04:52,722 --> 01:04:55,156
You've been back to the crime scene.

840
01:04:56,492 --> 01:04:58,824
Now isn't that interesting?

841
01:04:58,861 --> 01:05:01,261
Who gave you permission?

842
01:05:01,297 --> 01:05:04,994
The cat hair was only on one chair.

843
01:05:08,337 --> 01:05:10,271
Probably his favorite.

844
01:05:10,306 --> 01:05:13,901
Mmm. You know there was
something very strange though.

845
01:05:13,943 --> 01:05:16,173
- And what was that?
- There was no cat food in the house.

846
01:05:16,212 --> 01:05:18,578
There was no litter either.

847
01:05:19,949 --> 01:05:22,076
Well, he probably crapped outside.

848
01:05:22,118 --> 01:05:24,882
- What did he eat?
- Mice.

849
01:05:24,921 --> 01:05:26,718
He ate mice.

850
01:05:26,756 --> 01:05:28,189
I think that you planted that evidence.

851
01:05:28,224 --> 01:05:29,657
I think that you planted that cat fur.

852
01:05:31,994 --> 01:05:35,828
You get the fuck out of my office
right now.

853
01:05:35,865 --> 01:05:37,127
Why did you do it?

854
01:05:37,166 --> 01:05:39,930
Did you plant the evidence to ensure
Schaefer's conviction?

855
01:05:39,969 --> 01:05:41,960
Or where you covering something up?

856
01:05:42,004 --> 01:05:44,564
I didn't do a goddamn thing.

857
01:05:46,709 --> 01:05:48,506
But let me tell you something:

858
01:05:48,544 --> 01:05:51,513
If someone did, in theory,
do something

859
01:05:51,547 --> 01:05:55,449
to protect the public,
to close the book on a wretched killer,

860
01:05:55,484 --> 01:05:58,214
even if it was against the rules,
then I'd have to say

861
01:05:58,254 --> 01:06:01,451
this person did the right thing.

862
01:06:04,961 --> 01:06:08,328
Unless this person had the wrong guy

863
01:06:08,364 --> 01:06:11,663
and children continue to die.

864
01:06:17,473 --> 01:06:19,737
You know, I heard you were crazy.

865
01:06:23,512 --> 01:06:25,207
Now you go on now.

866
01:06:26,515 --> 01:06:27,982
Get out.

867
01:06:29,185 --> 01:06:31,119
Get out.

868
01:06:32,488 --> 01:06:35,787
Help us, Megan.

869
01:06:48,571 --> 01:06:50,664
Hey, you're that policewoman.

870
01:06:50,706 --> 01:06:52,697
Yeah.

871
01:06:52,742 --> 01:06:55,040
You're the bartender from Richmond's.

872
01:06:55,077 --> 01:06:56,704
Yeah, Hank.

873
01:06:56,746 --> 01:06:58,475
Good memory.

874
01:06:58,514 --> 01:07:02,075
You came in and spoke with Jay Castillo
a few times a couple years ago.

875
01:07:02,118 --> 01:07:03,881
Carla Castillo's father.

876
01:07:03,919 --> 01:07:05,887
That's right.
How's he doing?

877
01:07:05,921 --> 01:07:08,389
He stopped drinking.
It's a start.

878
01:07:08,424 --> 01:07:10,449
So you don't see
much of his anymore?

879
01:07:10,493 --> 01:07:12,688
Oh, I see him all the time.
We're neighbors.

880
01:07:12,728 --> 01:07:14,218
Did you know Carla?

881
01:07:14,263 --> 01:07:17,721
Yeah, nice kid.

882
01:07:19,068 --> 01:07:22,834
Did you notice anything different
about her before she was killed?

883
01:07:24,206 --> 01:07:25,764
No.

884
01:07:25,808 --> 01:07:27,935
Well, I didn't see much of her then.

885
01:07:27,977 --> 01:07:30,537
She stopped coming around
about six months earlier.

886
01:07:30,579 --> 01:07:33,173
What are you talking about?

887
01:07:33,215 --> 01:07:35,513
You didn't know?

888
01:07:35,551 --> 01:07:37,610
They had a big fight.

889
01:07:37,653 --> 01:07:40,679
Jay's drinking got pretty bad
at that point.

890
01:07:42,358 --> 01:07:44,986
- Listen, take care.
- Yeah, sure.

891
01:08:53,629 --> 01:08:56,257
Where'd Carla go
on Tuesday afternoons?

892
01:09:01,570 --> 01:09:04,038
It's been a long time.

893
01:09:04,073 --> 01:09:05,700
About two years.

894
01:09:05,741 --> 01:09:07,641
Why'd you lie, Jay?

895
01:09:11,747 --> 01:09:14,045
I was a shit father.

896
01:09:15,851 --> 01:09:18,115
I wasn't fit to take care of her,

897
01:09:18,154 --> 01:09:21,055
not even for a few hours.

898
01:09:24,994 --> 01:09:28,452
One night I got drunk...

899
01:09:32,368 --> 01:09:34,131
and I yelled at her.

900
01:09:35,671 --> 01:09:37,730
So bad...

901
01:09:40,809 --> 01:09:43,277
I had her go with
her grandmother after that.

902
01:09:44,647 --> 01:09:46,274
For how long?

903
01:09:46,315 --> 01:09:48,783
Six months or so.

904
01:09:49,785 --> 01:09:51,980
Why would your wife disapprove?

905
01:09:55,491 --> 01:09:57,482
My mother, she's...

906
01:09:57,526 --> 01:09:59,585
she's very Catholic.

907
01:09:59,628 --> 01:10:01,926
She gave Carla that necklace.

908
01:10:01,964 --> 01:10:03,864
And if my wife...

909
01:10:03,899 --> 01:10:05,560
Where did your mother
take her on Tuesdays?

910
01:10:05,601 --> 01:10:08,126
St. Michael's.

911
01:10:08,170 --> 01:10:10,764
A church in Rochester.

912
01:10:13,742 --> 01:10:15,903
- Ken: Megan.
- I found a connection.

913
01:10:15,945 --> 01:10:19,142
Carla went to St. Michael's on Tuesdays,
not her father's.

914
01:10:19,181 --> 01:10:21,672
Megan, you are in a world of shit.

915
01:10:21,717 --> 01:10:24,083
Norcross called me screaming
his head off about you.

916
01:10:24,119 --> 01:10:26,679
Ken. Ken, St. Michael's
is the connection.

917
01:10:26,722 --> 01:10:29,520
All three girls went there.
I'm going there right now.

918
01:10:29,558 --> 01:10:31,753
No, you are not.
You're coming in right now

919
01:10:31,794 --> 01:10:35,457
or I swear to God, I'm gonna send
a patrol car to that church to freakin'...

920
01:11:06,595 --> 01:11:08,722
Man: Now does your whole family
come to church

921
01:11:08,764 --> 01:11:10,857
or is it just you and your mom?

922
01:11:13,936 --> 01:11:15,995
Your dad too?

923
01:11:53,809 --> 01:11:55,834
Aren't you tired?

924
01:11:58,180 --> 01:12:00,580
No, it's not.

925
01:12:02,751 --> 01:12:04,844
No, she'd like to give you a kiss.

926
01:12:04,887 --> 01:12:07,048
It's true.

927
01:12:07,089 --> 01:12:09,114
So next year
you're gonna be in the choir.

928
01:12:09,158 --> 01:12:10,648
Yes.

929
01:12:10,693 --> 01:12:12,684
Why don't you go over there?

930
01:12:18,734 --> 01:12:20,463
My name is Megan Paige.

931
01:12:20,502 --> 01:12:23,471
I'm a detective with the Rochester
Police Department.

932
01:12:23,505 --> 01:12:25,769
I'm gonna need some information.

933
01:12:28,077 --> 01:12:29,840
Do you have any...?

934
01:12:33,549 --> 01:12:35,312
I need to talk to you.

935
01:12:37,619 --> 01:12:39,610
Of course.
This way.

936
01:12:48,497 --> 01:12:50,089
And I'm gonna need a list

937
01:12:50,132 --> 01:12:51,599
of everyone who's been involved

938
01:12:51,633 --> 01:12:54,295
in this church in the last five years...

939
01:12:54,336 --> 01:12:57,772
priests, parishioners, janitors,

940
01:12:57,806 --> 01:12:59,967
whoever else I'm not thinking of.

941
01:13:01,143 --> 01:13:03,111
You know the church

942
01:13:03,145 --> 01:13:05,079
will help the police
in any way we can,

943
01:13:05,114 --> 01:13:07,776
but I can't provide you with information
about our parishioners

944
01:13:07,816 --> 01:13:09,283
without permission.

945
01:13:09,318 --> 01:13:11,786
Can you call someone
and get that permission?

946
01:13:11,820 --> 01:13:13,617
I can try.

947
01:13:23,899 --> 01:13:26,367
Help, Megan.

948
01:13:27,703 --> 01:13:29,193
This is the place.

949
01:13:33,542 --> 01:13:35,635
Books.

950
01:13:42,551 --> 01:13:44,485
Do you pray for the girls?

951
01:13:44,520 --> 01:13:46,681
Excuse me?

952
01:13:46,722 --> 01:13:50,021
Do you pray for the angels
who were called back to heaven?

953
01:13:51,794 --> 01:13:54,592
Yes, I guess so.

954
01:13:57,466 --> 01:13:59,093
That's good.

955
01:14:11,780 --> 01:14:13,714
What the hell is this?

956
01:14:13,749 --> 01:14:15,740
They were our own angels.

957
01:14:21,123 --> 01:14:23,318
What is wrong with you?

958
01:14:24,393 --> 01:14:27,123
And what is that goddamn music?

959
01:14:28,764 --> 01:14:31,130
There's no music.

960
01:14:36,772 --> 01:14:39,741
- What? Fuck.
- Oh no.

961
01:14:39,775 --> 01:14:42,141
- Oh! Oh no.
- Fuck.

962
01:14:42,177 --> 01:14:43,804
- No, please.
- Who is this fuck?

963
01:14:43,846 --> 01:14:45,973
- Oh, please.
- What? God.

964
01:14:46,014 --> 01:14:48,539
God!

965
01:14:49,918 --> 01:14:52,011
No no no no no.

966
01:14:52,054 --> 01:14:54,181
I can hear you.
I can hear you.

967
01:14:57,192 --> 01:14:59,660
I can hear you!

968
01:14:59,695 --> 01:15:01,788
I know!

969
01:15:01,830 --> 01:15:04,492
But where?

970
01:15:17,079 --> 01:15:18,944
God!

971
01:15:39,167 --> 01:15:41,192
I can't take it.

972
01:15:46,208 --> 01:15:48,301
Megan!

973
01:16:45,567 --> 01:16:47,558
Wow.

974
01:16:47,603 --> 01:16:50,037
Déjà vu.

975
01:16:50,072 --> 01:16:52,563
Megan.

976
01:16:52,608 --> 01:16:54,439
How are you feeling?

977
01:16:57,045 --> 01:16:58,842
My head hurts.

978
01:17:04,119 --> 01:17:06,587
Was Captain Shine here?

979
01:17:06,622 --> 01:17:09,113
He left about five minutes ago.

980
01:17:10,792 --> 01:17:13,556
Shit.
I have to talk to him.

981
01:17:13,595 --> 01:17:15,563
He'll be back.

982
01:17:15,597 --> 01:17:17,895
Not good enough.

983
01:17:17,933 --> 01:17:20,561
Hold on, Meg.
You shouldn't leave.

984
01:17:20,602 --> 01:17:23,628
It's not what you need right now.

985
01:17:23,672 --> 01:17:26,641
Shouldn't leave or can't leave?

986
01:17:26,675 --> 01:17:29,542
Do you have a court order?

987
01:17:29,578 --> 01:17:31,307
We do.

988
01:17:31,346 --> 01:17:34,247
We have 14 days to observe you.

989
01:17:34,282 --> 01:17:36,716
But the point is we all want
what's best for you.

990
01:17:36,752 --> 01:17:38,413
We're all in this together.

991
01:17:41,423 --> 01:17:43,357
Did you put me on Thorazine?

992
01:17:43,392 --> 01:17:46,156
You were having a violent
episode when you arrived.

993
01:17:46,194 --> 01:17:49,493
- It's just to give you some clarity.
- Fuck that.

994
01:17:49,531 --> 01:17:51,158
Meg.

995
01:17:52,567 --> 01:17:54,933
Nurse, send Alex in here, please.

996
01:17:54,970 --> 01:17:56,938
Megan.

997
01:17:56,972 --> 01:17:58,564
You're delusional.

998
01:17:58,607 --> 01:18:01,201
It's the disease that makes
you want to do this.

999
01:18:01,243 --> 01:18:03,643
I'm a detective, Dr. Parks.
I have a case to solve.

1000
01:18:03,679 --> 01:18:07,080
You're not a detective, Meg.
You were a detective.

1001
01:18:07,115 --> 01:18:08,707
You're sick now.

1002
01:18:08,750 --> 01:18:10,650
I'm warning you, Dr. Parks,

1003
01:18:10,686 --> 01:18:13,712
do not impede this investigation.

1004
01:18:13,755 --> 01:18:16,417
You remember when you wanted
to kill yourself?

1005
01:18:17,492 --> 01:18:19,585
This is the same thing.

1006
01:18:19,628 --> 01:18:21,619
It's your sickness, Meg.

1007
01:18:21,663 --> 01:18:24,757
Megan. Meg.

1008
01:18:27,869 --> 01:18:30,804
Meg, let's just calm down

1009
01:18:30,839 --> 01:18:33,399
and think about what's best.

1010
01:18:33,442 --> 01:18:35,171
What do you want me to do?

1011
01:18:35,210 --> 01:18:36,905
Let her think.

1012
01:18:38,780 --> 01:18:40,771
Wait wait, Alex.
Wait. No!

1013
01:18:40,816 --> 01:18:43,216
Down. Down. Down.

1014
01:18:43,251 --> 01:18:45,242
Easy. Easy. Easy.

1015
01:18:50,759 --> 01:18:53,387
You follow me out
and I will break your other arm.

1016
01:18:53,428 --> 01:18:56,420
Dr. Park, you're a nice man

1017
01:18:56,465 --> 01:18:59,161
and I will not hit you
unless you come out of this room

1018
01:18:59,201 --> 01:19:00,998
before I'm gone.

1019
01:19:41,109 --> 01:19:43,236
They've got my house staked out.

1020
01:19:43,278 --> 01:19:44,711
They aren't messing around.

1021
01:19:44,746 --> 01:19:48,204
Well, listen, you can stay here
as long as you can stand the company.

1022
01:19:48,250 --> 01:19:50,650
Have you got a plan?

1023
01:19:50,685 --> 01:19:53,586
I'm gonna break into that church
and find their records.

1024
01:19:53,622 --> 01:19:55,886
Oh, Megan, I don't think
you're in any shape for that.

1025
01:19:55,924 --> 01:19:58,154
I feel okay.
I just need a nap.

1026
01:19:58,193 --> 01:20:01,959
Maybe it's the Thorazine,
but I can still tell what's real.

1027
01:20:01,997 --> 01:20:04,488
The pictures on the wall were real.

1028
01:20:06,134 --> 01:20:08,659
Don't you think the police
will be looking into the church

1029
01:20:08,703 --> 01:20:10,694
now that you've established a link?

1030
01:20:10,739 --> 01:20:12,297
Who knows?

1031
01:20:12,340 --> 01:20:16,470
They've found a way to botch
every other aspect of this investigation.

1032
01:20:16,511 --> 01:20:18,240
Maybe they're planning on giving

1033
01:20:18,280 --> 01:20:20,646
that creepy fucking priest
the keys to the city.

1034
01:20:26,121 --> 01:20:28,351
I sound like a lunatic.

1035
01:20:29,357 --> 01:20:31,621
No, you just need to get
